<HEAD>Earthquake Hits Remote Northern Quebec</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS thruout with new material and editing, slightly revising
exact time and force of earthquake, including Northwest Territories. No
pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MONTREAL (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake struck the <LOCATION>Ungava Peninsula</LOCATION>
of northern <LOCATION>Quebec</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Baffin Island</LOCATION> and the eastern part of the
<ORGANIZATION>Northwest Territories</ORGANIZATION> on <DATE>Christmas</DATE> <TIME>morning</TIME>, but no damage or
injuries were reported.
   The quake, which occurred at <TIME>9:24 a.m. EST</TIME>, measured 6.2 on the
Richter scale, said seismologist <PERSON>Robert North</PERSON> of the <LOCATION>Ottawa</LOCATION> office
of the <ORGANIZATION>Geological Survey of Canada</ORGANIZATION>.
   ``An earthquake over 6 points is a serious earthquake and can
cause severe damage in a populated area,'' North said.
   ``But fortunately the quake ... took place in a sparsely
populated area which has no large buildings, so the effects should
not cause any personal damage,'' he said.
   North said his office received a telephone call from the Inuit
village of <LOCATION>Igloolik</LOCATION> to report the quake. Iqaluit, on <ORGANIZATION>Frobisher Bay</ORGANIZATION>
in <LOCATION>Baffin Island</LOCATION>, also felt the temblor.
   Father <PERSON>Paul-Emile Tremblay</PERSON>, director of the <ORGANIZATION>Seismological
Observatory</ORGANIZATION> at <LOCATION>Montreal</LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION>Jean de Brebeuf College</ORGANIZATION>, said the
epicenter was in the eastern part of the <ORGANIZATION>Northwest Territories</ORGANIZATION> and
the quake was felt within a 620-mile radius.
   ``We have been noticing low-level tremors in that area for some
time, so we were not surprised by the strong earthquake which
occurred on <DATE>Christmas</DATE> <TIME>morning</TIME>,'' he said.
   The Richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an
earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph.
</TEXT>
